Usage: flattenPartition [-help] [<partitionName>] [-bringBackRow]
                        [-keepPinGeometry] [-noUninheritPhysical]

-help                    # Prints out the command usage
<partitionName>          # Specifies the name of the partition. You can specify
                         # any number of partitions. (string, optional)
-bringBackRow            # Specifies that partition row information should be
                         # brought back for certain cases. (bool, optional)
-keepPinGeometry         # Specifies that partition pin geometries should be
                         # retained. (bool, optional)
-noUninheritPhysical     # Specifies that physical only cell instances are
                         # removed during flattenPartition. (bool, optional)